name: Vanguard U.S. Dividend Appreciation Index ETF
longDescription: The investment objective of Vanguard U.S. Dividend Appreciation Index ETF (the ETF) is to track, to the extent reasonably possible and before fees and expenses, the performance of S&P U.S. Dividend Growers Index (the Index). The Index is a float adjusted market capitalization weighted index that consists of common stocks in the S&P United States BMI that have followed a policy of consistently increasing dividends every year for at least 10 years, subject to a dividend yield sustainability screen and a 4% company cap at the time of any rebalancing. To achieve its investment objective, the ETF employs a passive management, or indexing, investment approach designed to track the performance of the Index by investing primarily in a U.S.-domiciled fund managed by The Vanguard Group, Inc hat seeks to track the Index.
